---
title: Washing Chicken
slug: washing-chicken
---
A lot of recipes will tell you to _rinse chicken_ and _pat_ it _dry_. I _don't recommend_ this. Thorough _cooking kills_ the _food-borne illnesses_ present _in chicken_. So _washing_ raw chicken in the sink just _increases_ the _likelihood_ of _cross-contamination_ through _splashing water_.
